&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The human approves a structured action, not a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Step 7: Measure the workflow&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="step-7-measure-the-workflow"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#step-7-measure-the-workflow" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Track:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;escalation rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;approval rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;rejection rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;average handling time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SLA miss rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;model draft acceptance rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;reviewer edit distance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;repeat escalation reasons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;downstream user satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If escalation rate rises after a release, something changed. It may be model quality, retrieval quality, policy strictness, or traffic mix.&lt;/p&gt;
